The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 New Delhi, April 10 (PTI): The Central Information Commission has imposed a fine of Rs 13,000 on a doctor of a municipal hospital for delay in providing information on an RTI plea.

 The chief information commissioner penalised Madhu Jain, the public information officer of Hindu Rao hospital, holding her liable for a 52-day delay in disclosing information sought by Navin Neeraj and Subroto Roy over a file related to harassment.

 Kanpur (PTI): A 13-year-old boy hanged himself to death on Monday after watching a suicide scene in a serial. Pankaj, a class VIII student of Maswanpur area, hanged himself with a cloth while his family members were not at home, police said.

 Chennai (PTI): All new buildings in Tamil Nadu built by the government and private institutions will have ramps. This would ensure a barrier-free environment for the disabled, said the social welfare minister in the Assembly.

 Mumbai (PTI): The trial of Alistair Pereira, accused of running over seven labourers with his car last year, has begun. As his lawyer failed to appear in court, a fine of Rs 5,000 was imposed on the accused. The prosecution had brought nine witnesses, mostly from Andhra Pradesh.

 Jaisalmer (PTI): Internet cafe and PCO owners have been ordered to maintain records of all international calls and emails after reports of suspicious people using these facilities to send secret information outside the country eme-rged. The records should include the callers identity and address.

 Mumbai (PTI): Tension prevailed in Navi Mumbais Kaharghar area after an altercation between residents of a housing society and a group of boys from nearby Belpada village over pigeons. The boys were pelting stones at the pigeons that are often fed by the residents, two of whom were even beaten up.




